# Section comments (minimal, scannable)

When writing or editing FORJD code, mark logical sections with short comments so a reader can understand the file by scanning comments alone.

## Rules
- **Section headers** before each logical block (imports ok without; group the rest).
- **One line** preferred; two lines max. Say *what the section is for*, not how every line works.
- **Do not** narrate obvious syntax (`// increment i`, `# return result`).
- **Do** call out security boundaries, auth, E2EE (ciphertext-only), and non-obvious invariants.
- Keep module/file docstrings; section comments complement them.
- Match language style: `# --- Title ---` in Python/SQL/Rust; `// --- Title ---` in TS/JS.

## Example

```python
# --- JWT verification ---
def verify_supabase_jwt(token: str) -> AuthUser:
    ...

# --- FastAPI dependencies ---
async def get_current_user(...):
    ...
```

```typescript
// --- Encoding helpers ---
function b64Encode(bytes: Uint8Array): string { ... }

// --- Seal / open (AES-256-GCM) ---
export async function seal(...) { ... }
```

## When
- New files: add section comments as you write.
- Edits to existing files: add or fix section comments for the areas you touch (and nearby unmarked sections if small).
